&lt;Petranol Plc> said it was discussingthe takeover of an unnamed company owned by Frenchman HubertPerrodo in exchange for Perrodo taking a 51 pct stake inPetranol.    It said in a statement the assets of the company to beacquired included a "substantial interest" in an unspecified oilfield in Torrance, California, and five mln dlrs in cash.    Funding commitments for Petranol, both in respect of theCalifornian oil field and Petranol's existing U.S. Assets,would be included in the agreement. Petranol said the dealwould enhance its presence in the U.S., Increase its capitaland secure the availability of development cash. Reuter&#3;